## global_search

```
FUNCTION global_search(
    search_term text,
    param_tables text[] default '{}',
    param_schemas text[] default '{public}',
    progress text default null -- 'tables','hits','all'
) RETURNS table(schemaname text, tablename text, columnname text, rowctid tid)
```

`global_search` finds `search_term` in all tables of a database,
or in a subset delimited by the `param_tables` or `param_schemas`
parameters.

The progress is optionally reported by `raise info` messages.
When `progress` is 'tables' or `all``, each table searched into is reported.
When `progress` is `hits` or `all`, each hit is immediately reported,

In addition all hits are returned by the function in the form of a table-like
value: `(schemaname text, tablename text, columnname text, rowctid tid)`.

